const Q_IGBO_2010=[{"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>1", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">AGHỌTAAZAA <br/> Gụọ ederede atọ ndị a ma zaa ajụjụ niile sitere na ha. <br/>  <br/> Ederede I <br/> Uche echefuola asị ọ tụọrọ nne na nna Ebuka na ya ga-enyere ha aka zụọ Ebuka <br/> n'akwụkwọ.Ụmụ nke ya ga-anọ n'ụlọ, Ebuka ana-ejegharị ka atụrụ na-enweghị onye <br/> nche, na-erere nne ya ukwu mmiri maọbụ ahụekere. Ezumike adịghịrị Ebuka. Ọ lọta <br/> ahịa, okwu na ụka. Nne ya ukwu akụghị ya ihe na ọ nọtere aka, ọ maa ya akantị na Hausa <br/> o rechaghị ihe o bunyere ya ree. Ọ bụzi nwamkpọta na-achụtara ezinaụlọ Uche ihe ha <br/> na-eri? Ewo, Ụwa nwa ogbenye! Ọ bụrụ na aka dị nne na nna Ebuka arọ, ọ ga-anọ <br/> n'ọnọdụ ọjọọ a? <br/> Nke kachasị nke bụ orure a na-erezi ụmụaka n'oge a. Ndị ajọ mmadụ na-aga <br/> kpọrọ ụmụaka nọ n'agbata afọ ise ruo n' iriabụọ n'ime obodo. Ha na-atụrụ nne na <br/> nna ụmụntakịrị ndị a asị na ha ga-akpọga ha ebe ihe ga-adịrị ha mma ma zụọkwa ha <br/> n'akwụkwọ. <br/>  <br/> Isiokwu kwesịrị ederede a bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Igbu ụmụaka</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Mmegbu ụmụaka</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ịgba ụmụaka ohu</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ụmụaka anaghị eje akwụkwo.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The main theme of the passage is the suffering of children, particularly Ebuka, who is neglected by his parents and has to fend for himself. This is evident in the description of Ebuka's life, where he is likened to a sheep without a shepherd, and his parents are criticized for not providing for him. Therefore, the correct answer is 'Mmegbu ụmụaka' which translates to 'Oppression of children'.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>2", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGHỌTAAZAA <br/> Gụọ ederede atọ ndị a ma zaa ajụjụ niile sitere na ha. <br/>  <br/> Ederede I <br/> Uche echefuola asị ọ tụọrọ nne na nna Ebuka na ya ga-enyere ha aka zụọ Ebuka <br/> n'akwụkwọ.Ụmụ nke ya ga-anọ n'ụlọ, Ebuka ana-ejegharị ka atụrụ na-enweghị onye <br/> nche, na-erere nne ya ukwu mmiri maọbụ ahụekere. Ezumike adịghịrị Ebuka. Ọ lọta <br/> ahịa, okwu na ụka. Nne ya ukwu akụghị ya ihe na ọ nọtere aka, ọ maa ya akantị na Hausa <br/> o rechaghị ihe o bunyere ya ree. Ọ bụzi nwamkpọta na-achụtara ezinaụlọ Uche ihe ha <br/> na-eri? Ewo, Ụwa nwa ogbenye! Ọ bụrụ na aka dị nne na nna Ebuka arọ, ọ ga-anọ <br/> n'ọnọdụ ọjọọ a? <br/> Nke kachasị nke bụ orure a na-erezi ụmụaka n'oge a. Ndị ajọ mmadụ na-aga <br/> kpọrọ ụmụaka nọ n'agbata afọ ise ruo n' iriabụọ n'ime obodo. Ha na-atụrụ nne na <br/> nna ụmụntakịrị ndị a asị na ha ga-akpọga ha ebe ihe ga-adịrị ha mma ma zụọkwa ha <br/> n'akwụkwọ. <br/> 'Okwu na-ụka' n'ederede a pụtara</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ịpịa ịtalị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ịba mba</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nsogbu</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">akantị.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The passage illustrates the \"nsogbu\" (problems) of neglect, poverty, and child trafficking that affect vulnerable children and families</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>3", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGHỌTAAZAA <br/> Gụọ ederede atọ ndị a ma zaa ajụjụ niile sitere na ha. <br/>  <br/> Ederede I <br/> Uche echefuola asị ọ tụọrọ nne na nna Ebuka na ya ga-enyere ha aka zụọ Ebuka <br/> n'akwụkwọ.Ụmụ nke ya ga-anọ n'ụlọ, Ebuka ana-ejegharị ka atụrụ na-enweghị onye <br/> nche, na-erere nne ya ukwu mmiri maọbụ ahụekere. Ezumike adịghịrị Ebuka. Ọ lọta <br/> ahịa, okwu na ụka. Nne ya ukwu akụghị ya ihe na ọ nọtere aka, ọ maa ya akantị na Hausa <br/> o rechaghị ihe o bunyere ya ree. Ọ bụzi nwamkpọta na-achụtara ezinaụlọ Uche ihe ha <br/> na-eri? Ewo, Ụwa nwa ogbenye! Ọ bụrụ na aka dị nne na nna Ebuka arọ, ọ ga-anọ <br/> n'ọnọdụ ọjọọ a? <br/> Nke kachasị nke bụ orure a na-erezi ụmụaka n'oge a. Ndị ajọ mmadụ na-aga <br/> kpọrọ ụmụaka nọ n'agbata afọ ise ruo n' iriabụọ n'ime obodo. Ha na-atụrụ nne na <br/> nna ụmụntakịrị ndị a asị na ha ga-akpọga ha ebe ihe ga-adịrị ha mma ma zụọkwa ha <br/> n'akwụkwọ. <br/> Asị Uche tụọrọ nne na nna Ebuka bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">izụ ya n'akwụkwọ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ibidoro ya ahịa</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">idozi ọnọdụ ya</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ibidoro ya ọrụ.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The phrase 'Asị Uche tụọrọ nne na nna Ebuka' refers to Uche's plea to Ebuka's parents. In the passage, Uche is described as pleading with Ebuka's parents to take care of him and send him to school. Therefore, the correct answer is 'izụ ya n'akwụkwọ' which translates to 'his plea for education'.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>4", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGHỌTAAZAA <br/> Gụọ ederede atọ ndị a ma zaa ajụjụ niile sitere na ha. <br/>  <br/> Ederede I <br/> Uche echefuola asị ọ tụọrọ nne na nna Ebuka na ya ga-enyere ha aka zụọ Ebuka <br/> n'akwụkwọ.Ụmụ nke ya ga-anọ n'ụlọ, Ebuka ana-ejegharị ka atụrụ na-enweghị onye <br/> nche, na-erere nne ya ukwu mmiri maọbụ ahụekere. Ezumike adịghịrị Ebuka. Ọ lọta <br/> ahịa, okwu na ụka. Nne ya ukwu akụghị ya ihe na ọ nọtere aka, ọ maa ya akantị na Hausa <br/> o rechaghị ihe o bunyere ya ree. Ọ bụzi nwamkpọta na-achụtara ezinaụlọ Uche ihe ha <br/> na-eri? Ewo, Ụwa nwa ogbenye! Ọ bụrụ na aka dị nne na nna Ebuka arọ, ọ ga-anọ <br/> n'ọnọdụ ọjọọ a? <br/> Nke kachasị nke bụ orure a na-erezi ụmụaka n'oge a. Ndị ajọ mmadụ na-aga <br/> kpọrọ ụmụaka nọ n'agbata afọ ise ruo n' iriabụọ n'ime obodo. Ha na-atụrụ nne na <br/> nna ụmụntakịrị ndị a asị na ha ga-akpọga ha ebe ihe ga-adịrị ha mma ma zụọkwa ha <br/> n'akwụkwọ. <br/> he abụọ Ebuka ji anata mmesike n'aka nne ya ukwu bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">alọtaghị n'oge na erechaghị ihe e bunyere ya ree.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ilọta n'oge na irecha ihe e bunyere ya ree.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">alọtaghị n'oge na ibufu ihe e bunyere ya ree.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ịlọta n'oge na irefu ihe e bunyere ya ree.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ebuka anaghị alọ n'oge ma ọ naghị ere ihe nne ya nyere ya ree.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>5", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGHỌTAAZAA <br/> Gụọ ederede atọ ndị a ma zaa ajụjụ niile sitere na ha. <br/>  <br/> Ederede I <br/> Uche echefuola asị ọ tụọrọ nne na nna Ebuka na ya ga-enyere ha aka zụọ Ebuka <br/> n'akwụkwọ.Ụmụ nke ya ga-anọ n'ụlọ, Ebuka ana-ejegharị ka atụrụ na-enweghị onye <br/> nche, na-erere nne ya ukwu mmiri maọbụ ahụekere. Ezumike adịghịrị Ebuka. Ọ lọta <br/> ahịa, okwu na ụka. Nne ya ukwu akụghị ya ihe na ọ nọtere aka, ọ maa ya akantị na Hausa <br/> o rechaghị ihe o bunyere ya ree. Ọ bụzi nwamkpọta na-achụtara ezinaụlọ Uche ihe ha <br/> na-eri? Ewo, Ụwa nwa ogbenye! Ọ bụrụ na aka dị nne na nna Ebuka arọ, ọ ga-anọ <br/> n'ọnọdụ ọjọọ a? <br/> Nke kachasị nke bụ orure a na-erezi ụmụaka n'oge a. Ndị ajọ mmadụ na-aga <br/> kpọrọ ụmụaka nọ n'agbata afọ ise ruo n' iriabụọ n'ime obodo. Ha na-atụrụ nne na <br/> nna ụmụntakịrị ndị a asị na ha ga-akpọga ha ebe ihe ga-adịrị ha mma ma zụọkwa ha <br/> n'akwụkwọ. <br/> \"Aka ịdị arọ\" n' ederede a pụtara</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">aka ịnyị arọ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">inwe ego</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">aka ịbu ibu</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ịda ogbenye</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">In the passage, Ebuka's mother cannot support him because she lacks money.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>6", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nnenna bụ naanị nwanwaanyị nne ya Uruji mụtara. N'ihi ya, Uruji na ụmụ ya ndị <br/> nke nwoke zụtọrọ ya azụtọ. Ihe onye ọbụla nọ n'ụlọ ahụ na-achọ bụ ime ya obiọma. <br/> Azụbụike na Ugoọjị na-amụ ya ka nwa. Nnamdị na-ewelatara ya anụ ewi ụbọchị niile <br/> 5 [Please turn over <br/> B <br/> ya na ndị otu ya gburu ewi. Mgbe ọbụla ọ dị ha ka ọ chọrọ ibe akwa, Chikere na <br/> Ọfọeze na-azọ azọ onye ga-aga mara ihe na-eme ya. <br/> Ụmụnne Nnenna megidere ihe a, ruo na nne ha achọpụta na nwata a emebiela. <br/> Nke kacha wute Uruji bụ na Nnenna na-aju nri mgbe ọbụla a kpasuru ya nwaobere <br/> iwe. Oge ụfọdụ, ụmụnne ya ga na-ewere azụ dị n'ofe nke ha tinyekwuoro ya ma ya <br/> bụrụ na ọ jụghị iri nri. <br/> Otu ụbochị, Nnenna jụrụ iri nri n'ihi na nne ya rọrọ ya anya. Ozigbo nke a <br/> mere, Uruji buuru nri ahụ nye nkịta ya. Site n'ụtụtu ruo mgbede ụbọchị ahụ, <br/> Nnenna kwụgidere agụụ, anya agwọgharịa ya. Ịjụ nri kwụsịziri iso <br/> n'ihe ndị o ji eme nwa. <br/>  <br/> N' ederede a, odee mere ka a ghọta Uruji nwere ụmụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">atọ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">anọ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ise</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">isii</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">In this passage, the writer shows that Uruji has 6 children.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>7", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> Nnenna bụ naanị nwanwaanyị nne ya Uruji mụtara. N'ihi ya, Uruji na ụmụ ya ndị <br/> nke nwoke zụtọrọ ya azụtọ. Ihe onye ọbụla nọ n'ụlọ ahụ na-achọ bụ ime ya obiọma. <br/> Azụbụike na Ugoọjị na-amụ ya ka nwa. Nnamdị na-ewelatara ya anụ ewi ụbọchị niile <br/> 5 [Please turn over <br/> B <br/> ya na ndị otu ya gburu ewi. Mgbe ọbụla ọ dị ha ka ọ chọrọ ibe akwa, Chikere na <br/> Ọfọeze na-azọ azọ onye ga-aga mara ihe na-eme ya. <br/> Ụmụnne Nnenna megidere ihe a, ruo na nne ha achọpụta na nwata a emebiela. <br/> Nke kacha wute Uruji bụ na Nnenna na-aju nri mgbe ọbụla a kpasuru ya nwaobere <br/> iwe. Oge ụfọdụ, ụmụnne ya ga na-ewere azụ dị n'ofe nke ha tinyekwuoro ya ma ya <br/> bụrụ na ọ jụghị iri nri. <br/> Otu ụbochị, Nnenna jụrụ iri nri n'ihi na nne ya rọrọ ya anya. Ozigbo nke a <br/> mere, Uruji buuru nri ahụ nye nkịta ya. Site n'ụtụtu ruo mgbede ụbọchị ahụ, <br/> Nnenna kwụgidere agụụ, anya agwọgharịa ya. Ịjụ nri kwụsịziri iso <br/> n'ihe ndị o ji eme nwa. <br/> N' ederede a, otu na ndị a bụ ada Uruji.</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Chikere.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nnenna.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ọfọeze.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ugoọjị.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">From the passage, it is clear that Nnenna is Uruji's only daughter.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>8", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> Nnenna bụ naanị nwanwaanyị nne ya Uruji mụtara. N'ihi ya, Uruji na ụmụ ya ndị <br/> nke nwoke zụtọrọ ya azụtọ. Ihe onye ọbụla nọ n'ụlọ ahụ na-achọ bụ ime ya obiọma. <br/> Azụbụike na Ugoọjị na-amụ ya ka nwa. Nnamdị na-ewelatara ya anụ ewi ụbọchị niile <br/> 5 [Please turn over <br/> B <br/> ya na ndị otu ya gburu ewi. Mgbe ọbụla ọ dị ha ka ọ chọrọ ibe akwa, Chikere na <br/> Ọfọeze na-azọ azọ onye ga-aga mara ihe na-eme ya. <br/> Ụmụnne Nnenna megidere ihe a, ruo na nne ha achọpụta na nwata a emebiela. <br/> Nke kacha wute Uruji bụ na Nnenna na-aju nri mgbe ọbụla a kpasuru ya nwaobere <br/> iwe. Oge ụfọdụ, ụmụnne ya ga na-ewere azụ dị n'ofe nke ha tinyekwuoro ya ma ya <br/> bụrụ na ọ jụghị iri nri. <br/> Otu ụbochị, Nnenna jụrụ iri nri n'ihi na nne ya rọrọ ya anya. Ozigbo nke a <br/> mere, Uruji buuru nri ahụ nye nkịta ya. Site n'ụtụtu ruo mgbede ụbọchị ahụ, <br/> Nnenna kwụgidere agụụ, anya agwọgharịa ya. Ịjụ nri kwụsịziri iso <br/> n'ihe ndị o ji eme nwa. <br/> N' ederede a, 'na-amụ ya ka nwa' pụtara na a na-eme ya ka</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nwa a mụrụ ọhụrụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọ bụ naanị nwa a mụtara</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nwa a hụrụ n'anya</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọ bụ naanị ya bụ mmadụ.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">From the context of the passage, it can be inferred that the phrase 'na-amụ ya ka nwa' means 'treats her like a child'.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>9", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> Nnenna bụ naanị nwanwaanyị nne ya Uruji mụtara. N'ihi ya, Uruji na ụmụ ya ndị <br/> nke nwoke zụtọrọ ya azụtọ. Ihe onye ọbụla nọ n'ụlọ ahụ na-achọ bụ ime ya obiọma. <br/> Azụbụike na Ugoọjị na-amụ ya ka nwa. Nnamdị na-ewelatara ya anụ ewi ụbọchị niile <br/> 5 [Please turn over <br/> B <br/> ya na ndị otu ya gburu ewi. Mgbe ọbụla ọ dị ha ka ọ chọrọ ibe akwa, Chikere na <br/> Ọfọeze na-azọ azọ onye ga-aga mara ihe na-eme ya. <br/> Ụmụnne Nnenna megidere ihe a, ruo na nne ha achọpụta na nwata a emebiela. <br/> Nke kacha wute Uruji bụ na Nnenna na-aju nri mgbe ọbụla a kpasuru ya nwaobere <br/> iwe. Oge ụfọdụ, ụmụnne ya ga na-ewere azụ dị n'ofe nke ha tinyekwuoro ya ma ya <br/> bụrụ na ọ jụghị iri nri. <br/> Otu ụbochị, Nnenna jụrụ iri nri n'ihi na nne ya rọrọ ya anya. Ozigbo nke a <br/> mere, Uruji buuru nri ahụ nye nkịta ya. Site n'ụtụtu ruo mgbede ụbọchị ahụ, <br/> Nnenna kwụgidere agụụ, anya agwọgharịa ya. Ịjụ nri kwụsịziri iso <br/> n'ihe ndị o ji eme nwa. <br/> Onye na-ewetara Nnenna anụ ewi n' ederede a bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Azụbike</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ọfọeze</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nnamdị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ugoọjị.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">From the passage, it is clear that Nnamdị is the one who feeds Nnenna with ewi.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>10", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> Nnenna bụ naanị nwanwaanyị nne ya Uruji mụtara. N'ihi ya, Uruji na ụmụ ya ndị <br/> nke nwoke zụtọrọ ya azụtọ. Ihe onye ọbụla nọ n'ụlọ ahụ na-achọ bụ ime ya obiọma. <br/> Azụbụike na Ugoọjị na-amụ ya ka nwa. Nnamdị na-ewelatara ya anụ ewi ụbọchị niile <br/> 5 [Please turn over <br/> B <br/> ya na ndị otu ya gburu ewi. Mgbe ọbụla ọ dị ha ka ọ chọrọ ibe akwa, Chikere na <br/> Ọfọeze na-azọ azọ onye ga-aga mara ihe na-eme ya. <br/> Ụmụnne Nnenna megidere ihe a, ruo na nne ha achọpụta na nwata a emebiela. <br/> Nke kacha wute Uruji bụ na Nnenna na-aju nri mgbe ọbụla a kpasuru ya nwaobere <br/> iwe. Oge ụfọdụ, ụmụnne ya ga na-ewere azụ dị n'ofe nke ha tinyekwuoro ya ma ya <br/> bụrụ na ọ jụghị iri nri. <br/> Otu ụbochị, Nnenna jụrụ iri nri n'ihi na nne ya rọrọ ya anya. Ozigbo nke a <br/> mere, Uruji buuru nri ahụ nye nkịta ya. Site n'ụtụtu ruo mgbede ụbọchị ahụ, <br/> Nnenna kwụgidere agụụ, anya agwọgharịa ya. Ịjụ nri kwụsịziri iso <br/> n'ihe ndị o ji eme nwa. <br/> N' ederede a, otu na ndị a mere ka Nnenna kwụsị ịjụ nri.</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nkịta riri nri ya.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nne ya rọrọ ya anya.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nne ya kwụrụ ya agụụ.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ụmụnne ya kpasuru ya iwe.</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ụmụnne ya kpasuru ya iwe n'ihi na o mere ihe ha anaghị achọ.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>11", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ederede III <br/>  <br/> Oriakụ Dike bụ onye anyaukwu. Ọ bụkwa onye oke njenje n'agbanyeghị na di ya <br/> bụ akajiakụ n'obodo. Maka ndụ dị etu a, ụmụ ya niile kpọrọ ya asị, mana di ya hụrụ <br/> ya n'anya ma na-akwanyekwara ya aja n'ukwu n'ihe niile ọ na-eme. <br/> Afọ tara nwaanyị a mmiri. Ọ naghị eleba anya n'ezinaụlọ ya. Ọ nakwaghị <br/> elebara ụmụ ya anya n'ihe ọbụla ha na-eme. Ihe niile nwaanyị a ma na ndụ ya bụ <br/> ihe ọ ga-eme ka a nụ aha ya n'obodo ma ọ dị mma ma ọ dị njo. Naanị ihe ọ na-arụ <br/> bụ ije oke njenje na isogharị ndị ndọrọndọro ọchịchị, ịgagharị n'ụlọ dibịa dị icheiche <br/> na ịtu arọ ihe ọ ga-eme ka onye ọbụla nọrọ ya n'okpuru, ọkachasị ebe ụmụnwaanyị <br/> ibe ya nọ. <br/>  <br/> Gịnị bụ isiokwu ederede a?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nwaanyị anya ukwu.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nwaanyị ajọ agwa.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nwaanyị afọ tara mmiri.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nwaanyị oke njenje.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The theme of this text is bad character of a woman or the traits of a wicked woman. It talks about behaviors and qualities that cause a woman to be called wicked.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>12", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> Ederede III <br/>  <br/> Oriakụ Dike bụ onye anyaukwu. Ọ bụkwa onye oke njenje n'agbanyeghị na di ya <br/> bụ akajiakụ n'obodo. Maka ndụ dị etu a, ụmụ ya niile kpọrọ ya asị, mana di ya hụrụ <br/> ya n'anya ma na-akwanyekwara ya aja n'ukwu n'ihe niile ọ na-eme. <br/> Afọ tara nwaanyị a mmiri. Ọ naghị eleba anya n'ezinaụlọ ya. Ọ nakwaghị <br/> elebara ụmụ ya anya n'ihe ọbụla ha na-eme. Ihe niile nwaanyị a ma na ndụ ya bụ <br/> ihe ọ ga-eme ka a nụ aha ya n'obodo ma ọ dị mma ma ọ dị njo. Naanị ihe ọ na-arụ <br/> bụ ije oke njenje na isogharị ndị ndọrọndọro ọchịchị, ịgagharị n'ụlọ dibịa dị icheiche <br/> na ịtu arọ ihe ọ ga-eme ka onye ọbụla nọrọ ya n'okpuru, ọkachasị ebe ụmụnwaanyị <br/> ibe ya nọ. <br/> Nke ederede a na-eme bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nkọcha</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">otito</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ụta</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ndụmọdu.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The passage describes the traits of a wicked woman.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>13", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> Ederede III <br/>  <br/> Oriakụ Dike bụ onye anyaukwu. Ọ bụkwa onye oke njenje n'agbanyeghị na di ya <br/> bụ akajiakụ n'obodo. Maka ndụ dị etu a, ụmụ ya niile kpọrọ ya asị, mana di ya hụrụ <br/> ya n'anya ma na-akwanyekwara ya aja n'ukwu n'ihe niile ọ na-eme. <br/> Afọ tara nwaanyị a mmiri. Ọ naghị eleba anya n'ezinaụlọ ya. Ọ nakwaghị <br/> elebara ụmụ ya anya n'ihe ọbụla ha na-eme. Ihe niile nwaanyị a ma na ndụ ya bụ <br/> ihe ọ ga-eme ka a nụ aha ya n'obodo ma ọ dị mma ma ọ dị njo. Naanị ihe ọ na-arụ <br/> bụ ije oke njenje na isogharị ndị ndọrọndọro ọchịchị, ịgagharị n'ụlọ dibịa dị icheiche <br/> na ịtu arọ ihe ọ ga-eme ka onye ọbụla nọrọ ya n'okpuru, ọkachasị ebe ụmụnwaanyị <br/> ibe ya nọ. <br/> N' ederede a, 'afọ tara nwaanyị a mmiri na-akọwa na</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">mmiri adịghị ya n' afọ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">mmiri fọrọ ya n'afọ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọ naghị eme ebere</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">o nwere obi ebere.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">N'ederede a, 'afọ tara nwaanyị a mmiri' pụtara na Oriakụ Dike agbachaghị aka ilebara ezinụlọ ya anya kemgbe ogologo oge.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>14", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> Ederede III <br/>  <br/> Oriakụ Dike bụ onye anyaukwu. Ọ bụkwa onye oke njenje n'agbanyeghị na di ya <br/> bụ akajiakụ n'obodo. Maka ndụ dị etu a, ụmụ ya niile kpọrọ ya asị, mana di ya hụrụ <br/> ya n'anya ma na-akwanyekwara ya aja n'ukwu n'ihe niile ọ na-eme. <br/> Afọ tara nwaanyị a mmiri. Ọ naghị eleba anya n'ezinaụlọ ya. Ọ nakwaghị <br/> elebara ụmụ ya anya n'ihe ọbụla ha na-eme. Ihe niile nwaanyị a ma na ndụ ya bụ <br/> ihe ọ ga-eme ka a nụ aha ya n'obodo ma ọ dị mma ma ọ dị njo. Naanị ihe ọ na-arụ <br/> bụ ije oke njenje na isogharị ndị ndọrọndọro ọchịchị, ịgagharị n'ụlọ dibịa dị icheiche <br/> na ịtu arọ ihe ọ ga-eme ka onye ọbụla nọrọ ya n'okpuru, ọkachasị ebe ụmụnwaanyị <br/> ibe ya nọ. <br/> Otu na ndị a bụ eziokwu banyere ederede a</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Oriakụ na ụmụ ya niile bụ otu.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Oriakụ na ụmụ ya atọ bụ otu.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Oriakụ na di ya na ụmụ ya bụ otu.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Oriakụ na di ya Dike bụ otu.</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Oriakụ na di ya Dike bụ otu n'ihi na di ya hụrụ ya n'anya ma na-akwanyekwara ya ùgwù n'agbanyeghị àgwà ya.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>15", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> Ederede III <br/>  <br/> Oriakụ Dike bụ onye anyaukwu. Ọ bụkwa onye oke njenje n'agbanyeghị na di ya <br/> bụ akajiakụ n'obodo. Maka ndụ dị etu a, ụmụ ya niile kpọrọ ya asị, mana di ya hụrụ <br/> ya n'anya ma na-akwanyekwara ya aja n'ukwu n'ihe niile ọ na-eme. <br/> Afọ tara nwaanyị a mmiri. Ọ naghị eleba anya n'ezinaụlọ ya. Ọ nakwaghị <br/> elebara ụmụ ya anya n'ihe ọbụla ha na-eme. Ihe niile nwaanyị a ma na ndụ ya bụ <br/> ihe ọ ga-eme ka a nụ aha ya n'obodo ma ọ dị mma ma ọ dị njo. Naanị ihe ọ na-arụ <br/> bụ ije oke njenje na isogharị ndị ndọrọndọro ọchịchị, ịgagharị n'ụlọ dibịa dị icheiche <br/> na ịtu arọ ihe ọ ga-eme ka onye ọbụla nọrọ ya n'okpuru, ọkachasị ebe ụmụnwaanyị <br/> ibe ya nọ. <br/> 'Di ya na-akwanyere ya aja n'ukwu' n'ederede a pụtara na di ya</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">na-enye ya nsọpụrụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">na-eso ya agagharị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">na-akwado ya</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">wado ya</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Di ya na-akwanyere ya aja n'ukwu' n'ederede a pụtara na di ya na-asọpụrụ ya nke ukwuu ma na-enye ya otuto n'ihe niile ọ na-eme.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): COMPREHENSION (AGHỌTAAZAA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>16", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> Ederede III <br/>  <br/> Oriakụ Dike bụ onye anyaukwu. Ọ bụkwa onye oke njenje n'agbanyeghị na di ya <br/> bụ akajiakụ n'obodo. Maka ndụ dị etu a, ụmụ ya niile kpọrọ ya asị, mana di ya hụrụ <br/> ya n'anya ma na-akwanyekwara ya aja n'ukwu n'ihe niile ọ na-eme. <br/> Afọ tara nwaanyị a mmiri. Ọ naghị eleba anya n'ezinaụlọ ya. Ọ nakwaghị <br/> elebara ụmụ ya anya n'ihe ọbụla ha na-eme. Ihe niile nwaanyị a ma na ndụ ya bụ <br/> ihe ọ ga-eme ka a nụ aha ya n'obodo ma ọ dị mma ma ọ dị njo. Naanị ihe ọ na-arụ <br/> bụ ije oke njenje na isogharị ndị ndọrọndọro ọchịchị, ịgagharị n'ụlọ dibịa dị icheiche <br/> na ịtu arọ ihe ọ ga-eme ka onye ọbụla nọrọ ya n'okpuru, ọkachasị ebe ụmụnwaanyị <br/> ibe ya nọ. <br/> 'Nwa nwaanyị ka baa uru n'ezinaụlọ karịa nwa nwoke' bụ isiokwu n'edemede</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ekwumekwu</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">mgbagha</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nkọwami</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">mkparịtaụka.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The passage focuses on Oriakụ Dike's behavior, how she neglects her husband and children, and how she is more concerned with her reputation in the community, rather than comparing the value of a female child to a male child in the family. <br/> </div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>17", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ỤTỌASỤSỤ <br/>  <br/> Ụdaume nke adabaghị n'otu ụdamfe na ndị a bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">a</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">e</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The syllable that does not follow the same syllable pattern among them is /e/.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): GRAMMAR (ỤTỌASỤSỤ)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>18", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> ỤTỌASỤSỤ <br/> Okwu e nwere ndakọrịta ụdaume na ya na ndị a bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">agidi</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ejula</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ogbunigwe</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">okoroọbịa.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question is 'ogbunigwe'.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): GRAMMAR (ỤTỌASỤSỤ)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>19", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> ỤTỌASỤSỤ <br/> Agbọghọ ® Agbọọ bụ ọmụmaatụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ndapụ ụdaume</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ndapụ mgbochiume</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">olilo mgbochiume</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">olilo ụdaume.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question is 'ndapụ mgbochiume'.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): GRAMMAR (ỤTỌASỤSỤ)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>20", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> ỤTỌASỤSỤ <br/> N' ime mkpụrụokwu a bụ 'bịakọtara', mọfịm nnọọrọonwe bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">tara</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">bịa</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">bị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">bịakọ.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'bịa'.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): GRAMMAR (ỤTỌASỤSỤ)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>21", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> ỤTỌASỤSỤ <br/> Nke nwere nkejiokwu atọ na ndị a bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ntabianya</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">akwụkwọnri</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọkụko</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọchịchịrị.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'ọkụkọ'.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): GRAMMAR (ỤTỌASỤSỤ)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>22", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> ỤTỌASỤSỤ <br/> Mkpụrụokwu nwere myiriụdaume na ndị a bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">omere</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọnụma</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">naanị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">mkpụrụokwu.</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The word 'mkpụrụokwu' has ten vowels in it. In the Igbo language, vowels are 'a', 'e', 'i', 'o', 'u', 'ụ', 'ọ', 'ị', 'ǹ', 'ụ̣'. The word 'mkpụrụokwu' contains 'ụ' twice, 'o' once, 'u' once, 'k' once, 'w' once, which makes a total of ten vowels.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): GRAMMAR (ỤTỌASỤSỤ)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>23", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> ỤTỌASỤSỤ <br/> Anyị natara ngozi ya. N'ahịrịokwu a, 'anyị' bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">aha</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nkọwaaha</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nnọchiaha</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">mbuụzo.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'nnọchiaha'.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): GRAMMAR (ỤTỌASỤSỤ)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>24", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> ỤTỌASỤSỤ <br/> Na mkpụrụokwu a bụ 'agadaga' –d- bụ ọmụmaatu</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nsonaazụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nganiihu</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nnọniime</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nnọnetiti</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'nnọnetiti'.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): GRAMMAR (ỤTỌASỤSỤ)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>25", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> ỤTỌASỤSỤ <br/> Họta nke bụ mọfim njụ na ndị a</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">- ghị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">- ta</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">- ra</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">- kwa.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is '-ghị'.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): GRAMMAR (ỤTỌASỤSỤ)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>26", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> ỤTỌASỤSỤ <br/> Nke bụ ụbara na ndị a bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">gị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ha</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ya</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">mụ.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">In the Igbo language, 'ha' is the pronoun that translates to 'they' in English. The other options 'gị', 'ya', and 'mụ' translate to 'you', 'his/hers' and 'I/me' respectively.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): GRAMMAR (ỤTỌASỤSỤ)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>27", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> ỤTỌASỤSỤ <br/> Some friends of mine are missing from the audience. <br/> Nke tụgharịtara ahịrịokwu a bụ ụfọdụ ndị enyi m esoghị</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">na ndị a bịara ige ntị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">n'igwe mmadụ a</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">na ndị na-ege ntị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ndị bịara abịa.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The sentence 'Some friends of mine are missing from the audience' translates to 'Ụfọdụ ndị enyi m esoghị na ndị a bịara ige ntị' in Igbo. The phrase 'na ndị a bịara ige ntị' means 'among those that came to watch'. Therefore, the correct option is 'na ndị a bịara ige ntị'.</div>", "topic": "LAGUAGES (ASỤSỤ): GRAMMAR TRANSLATION (NTỤGHARỊ)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>28", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">AGỤMAGỤ <br/>  <br/> 'Ọ na-eme aka abụọ'. Nke a pụtara onye</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">asị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ohi</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ama</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ụjọ.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The phrase 'Ọ na-eme aka abụọ' in Igbo language translates to 'He is double-handed' in English. This is often used to describe someone who is deceitful or dishonest, hence the term 'ohi' which means 'thief' is the most appropriate answer. The other options 'asị' means 'lie', 'ama' means 'know' and 'ụjọ' means 'fear', none of which accurately describe the phrase.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>29", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> Otu na ndị a bụ okwu mgbawaọnụ.</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Gwa m gwa m gwa m ọkụchara aka baa ọhịa.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nwaanyị na-ere ọrụ ele ị na-ere ọrụ ele ere ka ị na-eri ọrụ ele eri?</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ọkpatara nkụ ahụhụ sịrị ngwere pụkwute ya ọrịrị.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Egbe bere, ugo bere, nke si ibe ya ebela, nku kwaa ya.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nwaanyị na-ere ọrụ ele, ị na-ere ọrụ ele, ere ka ị na-eri ọrụ ele.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>30", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> Nke gosịrị na ọ bụ akụkọ ifo ka a na-akọ bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">\"Otu mgbe...\"</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">\"Ụbọchị ahụ...\"</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">\"Chineke kere ụwa...\"</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">\"Ndị ụwa niile agbakọta...\"</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The phrase 'Agụmagụ' in Igbo language is a form of storytelling that usually starts with 'Otu mgbe...' which means 'Once upon a time...'. This is a common way to start folktales or stories in many cultures, including the Igbo culture.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>31", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> Otu ihe e ji mara Mahadum Odenigbo n' Ụwa Bụ Agha bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ikuku ọma ya</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">mmiri gbara ya gburugburu</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">eziokwu a na-ekwu na ya</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ezigbo nkụzi a na-akuzi na ya.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'ikuku ọma ya'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>32", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> Akụkọ a kọrọ n' Ụwa Bụ Agha bụ ihe mere</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">n'ime obodo</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">n'ụlọụka</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">na mahadum</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">na kọleji.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'na mahadum'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>33", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> N' Ụwa Bụ Agha, Prof. Ọdịlị gosịpụtara onwe ya dịka onye achọghị</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ịrụ ọrụ ya</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ịda mba n'ọrụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ibuso ihe ọjọọ agha</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ihe ọma na ndụ ya.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'ịda mba n'ọrụ'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>34", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> Onye dere Ụwa Mgbede bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">I.U. Nwadike</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">S.N. Okafo</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">C.C. Anọzie</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">T.U. Ubesie.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'S.N. Okafo'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>35", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> N'Ụwa Mgbede, Chigboo na Madụka chọtara Ọnwụdiwe ka</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọ chụọrọ ha aja</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọ gbazinye ha ego</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">o duje ha ikwunne ha</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọ gbaara ha kurutu</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'ọ gbaara ha kurutu'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>36", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> N'abụ 'Nwanne dị na Mba' dị n' Echiche, ụfọdụ mmadụ bi n'ụwa bụ akwụacha,ebe ụfọdụ bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọkazị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ede</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">akwụkwọ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">akịdị.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'ọkazị'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>37", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> N' abụ 'Ihe ụwa' dị n' Echiche, odeabụ mere ka anyị mara na onye chọrọ ka o <br/> nwetachaa ihe ụwa.</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">na-eso ihe ụwa ala</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">na-ụwa ala</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ga-akwado mkpụrụobi ya</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">na-atọ n'ime ụwa.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'na-eso ihe ụwa ala'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>38", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> N'abụ 'Ndụ Bụ Ekete' dị n' Echiche, 'Etu onye siri kpa ekete, ka o si eritere ya, ihe' pụtara na</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">etu onye siri kwado ndụ ya ka ndụ ya ga-adị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ụwa bụ ebe oriri na nkwari</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ekete na-enwetara mmadụ ihe nrite</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọ dị mma mmadụ inwetara onwe ya ihe.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The proverb is saying that life is a race and whoever wins should enjoy his life as it will be. This means that one should guard and cherish what they have earned or achieved in life, as it is a result of their efforts and struggles.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>39", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> N' Uche Bụ Akpa, ọkpụrụkpụ okwu odeabụ n'abụ 'Ọrụ Ugbo' bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">a rụsie ọrụ ike, e rijuo afọ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">e yiri efe ọma, a rụọkwa ọrụ ugbo</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Abakaliki kacha akọpụta ji</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">onye ọbụla gwube aka n'ala.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'a rụsie ọrụ ike, e rijuo afọ'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>40", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> N' 'Akọ Bụ Ndụ' n' Uche Bụ Akpa anụ a kpọrọ aha bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ngwere</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">oke</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">mbe</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ogwumagala</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'ogwumagala'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>41", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> Otu isiokwu pụtara ihe na Nka Dị Na Ntị bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Otu isiokwu pụtara ihe na Nka Dị Na Ntị bụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">'Ebe onye ọsọ ruru, onye ije ga-eru ya,</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">'Nwaanyị lụọ di abụọ, ọ họrọ nke ka ya mma'</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">'Nke onye metara, ya ji isi ya buru</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'Nke onye metara, ya ji isi ya buru'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>42", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> Na Nka Dị Na Ntị, ndị mmadụ bịara be Azụbụike n'ihi na</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nwa ya nwoke lọtara</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ahụ adịghị ya</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nwa ya nwụrụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọ zụrụ ụgbọala.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'nwa ya nwụrụ'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>43", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> Na Nka Dị Na Ntị, aha diọkpara Ọjị nke nọ Ala Bekee bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Njọkụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Azụbụike</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Amaechi</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Chima.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'Amaechi'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>44", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> Arụsị kwupụtara ihe ọjoo niile Oriakụ mere n'Obidiya bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Igwekaala</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ibini-Ụkpabị</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ọzụzụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Agbala.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'Ọzụzụ'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>45", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> AGỤMAGỤ <br/> Nrọ Obidiya rọrọ n'Obidiya metụtara</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọnwụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ndụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">agha</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ụlọikpe.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'ọnwụ'.</div>", "topic": "LITERATURE (AGỤMAGỤ): ORAL LITERATURE"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>46", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">OMENALA NA EWUMEWU <br/>  <br/> Onye na-ejikarị ọfọ ụmụnna bụ onye kacha</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">bụrụ okenye</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nwee ego</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">maa mma</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">too ogologo.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">In Igbo tradition, the person who holds the family's Ofo is considered the eldest. The Ofo is a sacred symbol of authority, truth, and justice in Igbo culture. Therefore, the person who holds it is usually the eldest or the head of the family. Hence, the correct answer is 'bụrụ okenye' which translates to 'is the eldest'.</div>", "topic": "GENERAL AND CURRENT AFFAIRS (IHE NDỊ NA-EME UGBUA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>47", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> OMENALA NA EWUMEWU <br/> Oge e ji egwu egwuọnwa bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">n'ụtụtụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">n'ehihie</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">na mgbede</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">n'abalị.</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Egwu Egwuonwa is a traditional dance in the Igbo culture that is performed at night during festivals or other important events. Therefore, the correct answer is 'n'abalị', which translates to 'at night'.</div>", "topic": "GENERAL AND CURRENT AFFAIRS (IHE NDỊ NA-EME UGBUA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>48", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> OMENALA NA EWUMEWU <br/> Nke ya na ọjị na-agakọrịta bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ọkụkọ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">nzu</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">ewu</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">mmiri.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">In Igbo culture, 'nzu' is a kind of chalk used in traditional rites including the breaking of kola nut. It is often used alongside the kola nut in these rites.</div>", "topic": "GENERAL AND CURRENT AFFAIRS (IHE NDỊ NA-EME UGBUA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>49", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> OMENALA NA EWUMEWU <br/> Obodo na-akọpụta osikapa na ndị a bụ</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Asaba</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Owere</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ihiala</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Abakalịkị.</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Abakaliki is known for its massive rice production. The town has a large number of rice milling industries and is considered one of the largest producers of rice in Nigeria.</div>", "topic": "GENERAL AND CURRENT AFFAIRS (IHE NDỊ NA-EME UGBUA)"}, {"id": "objective>Igbo>2010>50", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\"> <br/> OMENALA NA EWUMEWU <br/> Mgbe e ji eme ekwumekwu Odenigbo kwa afọ bụ n'ọnwa</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ọgọstụ</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Septemba</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ọktoba</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Nọvemba.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct answer to the question provided above is 'Septemba'.</div>", "topic": "GENERAL AND CURRENT AFFAIRS (IHE NDỊ NA-EME UGBUA)"}];
